===========================================================================
WHY CC-BY-4.0 FOR OPEN STANDARDS?
===========================================================================

The Airymax Open Standards are designed to be adopted as widely as
possible by the global AI Agent ecosystem. By using CC-BY-4.0 (the most
permissive Creative Commons license that requires only attribution):

  1. Any third party (commercial or non-commercial) can implement these
     standards without license fees or legal complications.
  2. Implementations can be open-source (any license) or proprietary
     (closed-source).
  3. The standards can be incorporated into industry consortia, ISO/IEC
     standards, or other standards bodies.
  4. The copyleft restrictions of AGPL v3 do NOT apply, ensuring maximum
     adoption.

This is consistent with industry practice for open standards such as:
  - W3C standards (released under W3C Document License, similar terms)
  - IETF RFCs (released under BSD-like terms)
  - Linux Standard Base (LSB) specifications

